# CHANGELOG — first-20-hours

---

## 2026-05-20

**Problem:** `claude:generateSkill` was returning a JSON parse error ("Expected ',' or '}' after property value in JSON at position 3769") when generating a plan. Response was being truncated before the JSON closed.
**Fix:** Increased `max_tokens` from 6000 to 8000 on the `claude:generateSkill` IPC handler in `electron/main.ts`. Split the JSON parse into its own try/catch that logs the raw response, length, and stop_reason to the console when parse fails, and surfaces a useful error message to the renderer.
**Reason:** 6000 tokens was not enough for complex skills with full schema (8 arrays, 7 weekly focus blocks, 10 competency questions). Stop reason was `max_tokens`, not `end_turn`.
**Result:** Plan generation no longer truncates. Parse failures now include actionable debug output in the Electron main process console.

**Problem:** `detectAssessmentType` and `generateRubric` calls in `AIGeneratorPanel.tsx` used `(window.api.claude as any)` casts because `detectAssessmentType` was missing from the `WindowAPI` type in `src/types/index.ts`.
**Fix:** Added `detectAssessmentType` to `WindowAPI.claude` in `types/index.ts`. Removed both `as any` casts in `AIGeneratorPanel.tsx`.
**Reason:** `preload.ts` already exposed `detectAssessmentType`; the type was just never updated. `generateRubric` was already typed so its cast was dead code.
**Result:** Full type safety across the IPC bridge. No more `as any` in the Claude API calls.

**Problem:** HANDOFF.md, STATUS.md, ROADMAP.md, and CHANGELOG.scroll were absent from the project, violating the MTW session protocol in CLAUDE.md.
**Fix:** Created all four files with accurate current-state content.
**Reason:** Required by CLAUDE.md global context rules.
**Result:** Session handoff docs are now present and accurate.

---

## 2026-05-20 (session 2)

**Problem:** `web/index.html` used three browser `prompt()` calls for API key entry (init, callClaude re-auth) and new skill creation. Blocks the browser thread, ignores tab focus, broken UX.
**Fix:** Replaced all three with a Promise-based modal system using the file's existing CSS variables. Modal overlays at z-index 200. ESC and clicking outside both close/cancel. API key modal shows/hides the key, displays current masked key when one exists. Init no longer blocks render.
**Reason:** `prompt()` is deprecated UX that clashes with the dark theme and cannot be styled.
**Result:** No more browser dialogs. Modal reused for both init and mid-session key prompts via Promise resolution.

**Problem:** `callClaude()` default `max_tokens` was 6000. Same truncation risk as the Electron bug fixed in session 1.
**Fix:** Changed default to 8000.
**Reason:** Plan generation calls `callClaude` without an explicit token count. Matches the Electron fix.
**Result:** Consistent token budget across both platforms.

**Problem:** URL edit input was missing from selfcorrect cards in the web phase board. Cards showed URL as a link if stored but there was no way to add or edit it.
**Fix:** Added URL input field scoped to `selfcorrect` phase in `cardHTML`, matching Electron behavior.
**Reason:** selfcorrect cards hold resource links. Without an edit field the feature was half-broken.
**Result:** URL input shows only on selfcorrect cards.

**Problem:** API key was not accessible after initial setup without opening devtools.
**Fix:** Added "api key" button to sidebar bottom actions panel, calling `showApiKeyModal(true)`.
**Reason:** Key management must be reachable without a page reload.
**Result:** Key change available at any time from sidebar.

---

## 2026-05-20 (session 4)

**Problem:** Skill name was entered three times: wizard, pre-commit goal, and AI generator skill input. Wizard value was not carried forward to the other two fields.
**Fix:** `emptySkill()` in `storage.ts` now sets `commit.goal = name`. Web `modalCreateSkill()` also sets `commit.goal = name`. Both platforms: one entry, pre-populated everywhere.
**Reason:** Pre-commit goal and AI generator seed the Claude prompt. Users were re-typing the same string three times with no added value.
**Result:** Skill name typed once. Pre-commit goal and AI generator field auto-populate on skill creation.

**Problem:** Web version lacked an onboarding wizard. First-time users saw a bare API key modal with no context, explanation, or skill setup flow.
**Fix:** Full multi-step wizard added to `Web/index.html`: welcome screen, API key instructions with console link, key entry with live connection test, first skill name input. Uses existing dark theme CSS variables throughout. Wizard shows on `!apiKey`, hides after completion. Old `showApiKeyModal(true)` init replaced.
**Reason:** Matches the Electron onboarding flow. New users need context about what the app does and what credentials are required.
**Result:** Consistent first-run experience across both platforms.

**Problem:** No per-user isolation. All users on the same machine shared one API key and one skills file.
**Fix:** Multi-user support added to Electron. Each user gets `skills-{username}.json` and a separate API key entry in the encrypted store. Migration runs on first launch: single-user data moves to user `default`. Startup shows user selector when multiple users exist, new user flow when zero users exist. User display and switch button added to sidebar.
**Reason:** Required for shared-machine use cases and family/class deployments.
**Result:** Full user isolation. Existing data migrates automatically to `default` profile.

**Problem:** JSON import had no user handling. Importing a backup silently merged data with no choice about where it went.
**Fix:** Electron JSON import now shows a 3-way choice: append to current profile, create new profile from this file (with username prompt), or cancel. Web JSON import shows replace all, merge, or cancel when current session has data.
**Reason:** Destructive imports without confirmation are a data loss risk.
**Result:** Import is always a deliberate action with explicit choice.

**Problem:** Test skills from development (`Learn 100 phrases in conversation Russian`) were present in `skills.json`.
**Fix:** `skills.json` cleared to `{}`. No hardcoded test skills found in source (only placeholder text in input fields). `devReset()` added to web version for console-level data wipe.
**Reason:** App must ship with no pre-existing data.
**Result:** App starts completely empty on next launch. Web version provides `devReset()` for local testing cleanup.

---

## 2026-05-20 (session 3)

**Problem:** `SessionLogPanel.tsx` only captured date, hours, and note. The `SessionEntry` type has had `focus`, `errors`, `fixes`, `evidence`, and `nextStep` since v1.3. The form was a regression — the type existed, the web version had the fields, the Electron form did not.
**Fix:** Added all five missing fields to the form (focus input, notes textarea, errors/fixes grid of textareas, evidence input, next step input). Updated `submit()` to parse errors/fixes/evidence as newline-split string arrays matching the `string[]` type. Updated entry display to render all fields: focus as the entry title, note below it, errors in accent, fixes in success, evidence in blue, next step in dim.
**Reason:** Type regression. `Omit<SessionEntry, 'id'>` was being satisfied with only 3 of 8 fields.
**Result:** Electron session log now matches web version field-for-field. Existing entries without the new fields render correctly since all are optional.
